Feature: Named Entity Recognition (NER) with Contextual Disambiguation
Motivation: To improve the accuracy of entity recognition by considering the surrounding context, which can help distinguish between entities with similar names but different meanings.
Behavior change: The pipeline will now include a contextual disambiguation step that uses the surrounding text to correctly identify and classify entities, reducing false positives and negatives.
Patch:
```
- Integrate a contextual disambiguation model into the NER component of the pipeline.
- Modify the NER training process to include context-aware examples.
- Update the entity recognition output to include context-based entity types and confidence scores.
- Refine the postprocessing step to handle the additional context-based entity information.
```
Test:
Before: A text with the entity "Apple" might be incorrectly classified as a fruit when it refers to the company.
After: The same text would correctly classify "Apple" as a company with a high confidence score, based on the surrounding context indicating a business setting.
```Java
public class ContextualDisambiguationNER {
    private ContextualDisambiguationModel model;

    public ContextualDisambiguationNER(ContextualDisambiguationModel model) {
        this.model = model;
    }

    public EntityType analyzeEntityWithContext(String text, int startIndex, int endIndex) {
        String context = extractContext(text, startIndex, endIndex);
        return model.disambiguateEntity(text, startIndex, endIndex, context);
    }

    private String extractContext(String text, int startIndex, int endIndex) {
        // Pseudo-code to extract the context around the entity
        return text.substring(startIndex - 5, endIndex + 5);
    }
}
```

