// Example Java code snippet for integrating NER with contextual linking
import org.nlp.entity.NERModel;
import org.nlp.knowledgebase.KnowledgeBaseAPI;

public class NERWithLinking {
    private NERModel nerModel;
    private KnowledgeBaseAPI knowledgeBaseAPI;

    public NERWithLinking(NERModel nerModel, KnowledgeBaseAPI knowledgeBaseAPI) {
        this.nerModel = nerModel;
        this.knowledgeBaseAPI = knowledgeBaseAPI;
    }

    public KnowledgeBaseEntity[] analyze(String text) {
        String[] entities = nerModel.recognizeEntities(text);
        KnowledgeBaseEntity[] linkedEntities = new KnowledgeBaseEntity[entities.length];

        for (int i = 0; i < entities.length; i++) {
            linkedEntities[i] = knowledgeBaseAPI.linkEntity(entities[i]);
        }

        return linkedEntities;
    }
}
```
In this example, `NERModel` and `KnowledgeBaseAPI` are hypothetical classes representing the NER model and the knowledge base API, respectively. The `analyze` method takes a piece of text, recognizes entities, and then links them to the knowledge base, returning an array of `KnowledgeBaseEntity` objects that contain both the entity and its linked context.

